---
import RootLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";
---

<RootLayout>
  <div class="readmeDiv sm:p-5 p-10">
    <center>
      <img
        src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Zigistry/Zilite/main/assets/logo.png"
        alt="Zilite Logo"
      />
    </center>

    <h2>Yet another code highlighter.</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Uses no dependencies.</li>
      <li>You can contribute more programming languages.</li>
      <li>Is extremely small size.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to use?</h2>
    <p>Just see the following example:</p>

    <h3>For basic HTML:</h3>

    <pre><code class="language-html">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;

&lt;html&gt;

&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/zilite@0.0.25/src/styles/darkMode.css" /&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;

&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="language-zig nice-code-block"&gt;
        const zilite:[]const u8 = "Syntax Highlighter";
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;script type="module"&gt;
        import &lcub; highlightElements &rcub; from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/zilite@0.0.25";
        import &lcub;zig &rcub; from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/zilite@0.0.25/src/language/zig.js";
        highlightElements(zig, "language-zig");
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;

&lt;/html&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h3>For use as a node module:</h3>

    <pre><code class="language-bash">
npm i zilite
    </code></pre>

    <pre><code class="language-javascript">
import * as hl from "higherlight";
import &lcub; zig &rcub; from "higherlight/src/language/zig";

const highlightedCode = hl.highlight(zig, "const x = 'asdf';");
console.log(highlightedCode);
    </code></pre>

    <p>
      Understood? Or still confused? Create a new issue and clear your doubts.
    </p>

    <h2>Contributing:</h2>

    <p>Please ⭐️ this repo, create pull requests, issues, etc.</p>
  </div>
</RootLayout>
